[I2I:DELIVERABLE] Forgemaster — SonarVision Mega Enhancement Push

## Summary
Complete overhaul of SonarVision repo for broad appeal. Every major feature
a production project needs: CLI, Docker, CI/CD, API docs, benchmarks,
gallery, notebook, landing page, monitoring, contributing guide.

## What Was Delivered
11 new files, 1612 lines of production code:

1. **CLI Tool** (sonar-vision-cli.py, 210 lines)
   - Commands: predict, train, visualize, serve, benchmark, config
   - argparse with colored help, logging, error handling
   
2. **Docker Infrastructure** (2 files)
   - Multi-stage Dockerfile: builder → production → dev targets
   - Full docker-compose.yml with API, Redis, Prometheus, Grafana, Jupyter
   
3. **CI/CD Pipeline** (.github/workflows/ci.yml)
   - Lint (ruff + mypy), Test (pytest + tox matrix), Docker build/push
   - GPU integration tests, deploy to production on main
   
4. **API Documentation** (docs/API.md)
   - Full REST API reference, WebSocket streaming, authentication
   - SDK examples (Python, curl), error codes, rate limits
   
5. **Benchmark Suite** (benchmarks/run_benchmarks.py)
   - Statistical perf measurement with warmup + sampling
   - Benchmarks: inference, encoding, decoding, water physics
   
6. **Gallery Page** (docs/gallery.html)
   - Professional showcase with 6 use case cards and stats
   - Dark theme matching the brand
   
7. **Demo Notebook** (demo/sonar-vision-demo.ipynb)
   - End-to-end walkthrough: load data → physics → encode → decode → viz
   
8. **Landing Page** (index.html)
   - Responsive marketing site with animated background
   - Hero, features grid, architecture flow, use cases, stats bar, CTA
   
9. **Contributing Guide** (CONTRIBUTING.md)
   - Development workflow, testing guidelines, PR template
   
10. **Monitoring** (monitoring/prometheus.yml)
    - Prometheus scrape config for API metrics

## Status
- SonarVision pushed to github.com/SuperInstance/sonar-vision (main)
- Node 24 set as default (nvm alias default 24)
- Minimax MCP working (2 tools: web_search, understand_image)
- Gateway running on Node 22 (fine, backward compatible)

